Three men accused of stealing goats and sheep appeared briefly in the Groot Marico Magistrate s Court on Tuesday, North West police said. Lieutenant Colonel Pelonomi Makau said the case against Letlhogonolo Motsusi, 20, Karabo Molefi, 18, and Selebaleng Motsusi, 21, was postponed to April 25 for formal bail application. The trio s court appearance for stock theft, follows their arrest on Sunday, [16 April 2017] at Reboile informal settlement in Groot Marico by Lehurutshe Stock Theft Unit members who acted on a tip-off, she said. The suspects are linked to cases of stock theft in which approximately 100 goats and sheep were stolen at farms in and around Groot Marico between March and April 2017. 